No matter what, you're past will always come back to haunt you. I wish it didn't have to be this way. I wish that things could be at least civil. I think perhaps there was too much bloodshed for that. I don't understand how anyone could think that this could all be fixed. They've tortured me in my sleep since they broke away from my life. I haven't forgotton about them, as much as I would like to. The truly scary thoughts have just recently come to mind. I was able to let go of Jonathan because I knew he had every right in the world to hate me, but I had forgiven myself for the mistakes I made. I have been able to feel nothing for him but the slight annoyance at his stupidity. Is this how Nina feels about me? Is this why she never even feigned an attempt? If so..then I know that there could be no way to reconcile, as I could never see Jonathan and I being able to be friends again. I just thought we had a deeper relationship than that. I really hate having to deal with this shit all over again. I just want to be able to enjoy the wonderful life I now have for myself without all of this bullshit. Have I killed myself yet? HAH. No way in hell I'd give up all I have goin for me. It's just a shame everything had to go sour between all of us in order for me to get where I am today. I do miss the friendships I have lost. These losses will never leave my heart.

She's gone. I know she's only 2 hours away, but I want nothing more than for her to be holding me right now. Thursday is so far away, and I don't want to think of what it will take to make it that long without seeing her smile. I don't think we've spent more than 24 hrs away from each other since the summer began. Now we have to get used to a whole week. Why does love come at such a price? Such agony for such rapture. It's like a drug, and I have an addictive personality...so says my last counselor. I pray that this will become easier- having to say goodbye to the one I love over and over again. I'm so afraid that I will fuck up the best thing I could have ever imagined. I wanted so badly to be able to fix myself before entering another relationship, but believe that this is what was meant to be. They always say you find true love when you arent looking for it...I just know that I'm totally ill-prepared. Why does fate always add a fucked up twist to everything? I just need something to numb the pain I feel right now. The true remedy has left and is currently living in Bowling Green. Why wont the sun hurry and signal a new day, one closer to that upon which I will be reunited with my other half?

"Fools rush in where angels fear to tread."
 
This reminds me of camp. All the fond memories of Sycamore Hills will forever be tainted by my this past summer. Though I had previously been exposed to a fair amount of bullshit in the way that things tended to happen at camp, never did I truly imagine that such ignorant hypocrisy could actually manifest itself  at a place so devoted to "growing on the inside by being outside." Though with the scarce amount of respect, trust, and freedom that was given, I don't know why I ever expected anything more.

Girl Scout Promise (which we recited every day at flag): On my honor, I will try to serve God and my country,to help people at all times*,and to live by the Girl Scout Law.
*In the event that you must make a minor infraction to a camp rule in order to hold true to this Promise, you will be punished for doing what is right.

Obviously, they forgot to clue me in on that last bit. Guess they assumed that a group of young, philanthropic women would stop at nothing to get the job done. How they could expect anyone to sit back and do nothing to help someone you had been working closely with for two months is beyond me. I also don't understand how camp life...can be disconnected from your personal life, at least to the point where if you saw a loved one loaded in an ambulance, you wouldn't need more than an hour or so to return to one of the most stressful working environments imaginable. If anyone who has worked at camp could please explain that one to me, I'd be most appreciative.

Damn me for having a heart full of love that commands me to stand up for what I know is right.

For some reason I felt this epiphany was beautiful and continued to gaze at the plant, not even caring of the fact I didn't know which, for awhile longer. These are the feelings I feel seperate me from some people. Not many see the beauty (and humor) in simplicity. Sometimes, this is all that gets me through the day. 
It's either that, or I'm making shit up in my head. Either way, thank Bob for simplicity /insanity /whatever.

Thanks for a great night, Terry...and for understanding my womanly psychoticness.

White lies only make yourself feel better. They still hurt when the truth is discovered, as with any lie. Lies, white or black, are like a drug; if you can't control yourself you use them far too often and end up hurting yourself and others. Honesty is all I have left to tolerate.

I can't sleep. Seeing Adrian at Kroger thrust the memory of what happened last Tuesday from hiding. It's so hard to accept two of the 3 people you cared for more than youself didn't reciprocate such feelings. It's hard to concieve of giving so much, only to have everything taken away. It's going to take so much work to undo the damage they have done- to be able to get that close with anyone else again. This relentless cylce will be the death of me. I feel like the waves that crash on every shore of every continent. At the high tide, I'm drug closer to safety and security, and then but a few hours pass before the low tide comes and I'm drug back out to sea to be swallowed whole by some random serpent, all due to the gravitational force of the Moon.
Oh yeah...today was my first day of complete sobriety. Hopefully, many more will follow.

So what am I supposed to do now? What path can I take that will lead me to happiness. How do I escape the cycle of failure, dissapointment, and pain? How can one action seem  to nullify all words that have been said in contradiction? I want help. I'm so tired of asking and not recieving. I'm going for the third try to see a counselor on monday. So much of my life has been drastically changed within the past 7 months. I need sunshine. I need a savior. I need a sense of stability and confidence in my existence. I need the emotional rollercoaster of the adolescent phase of life to end. I'm so scared I'll never be able to be the person I once was. I'll never be the Sassy people remember. The side of myself that I'd like to be all the time is dissipating in the wake of this disease that is slowly eating away at my soul.

<u>16 yrs old;summer before sophomore year</u>: I meet Nina for the first time...I think to get weed. Terry was supposed to hook us up.
<u>following year</u>: We become close friends. I hang out almost always with her.
<u> 17 yrs old; 2nd semester, junior year</u>: Nina steals money from her dad, he suspects me, Nina does not confess, and as a result, her father forbids me to see her. I felt most betrayed and ceased to consider her a friend.
<u>17 yrs old, end of 1st semester, senior year</u>: Jonathan has come into the picture, and reintroduces Nina and I.
<u>18 yrs old, 2nd semester, senior year</u>: Nina convinces her father it was Heath who stole the money& we are reunited as best friends again.
<u>18 yrs old</u> Jonathan and I hook up.
<u>18 yrs old, end of 1st semester college</u>Jonathan tells me he no longer thinks we should be friends, and my world is completely shot to hell.
<u> a mere few hours ago</u> My best friend tells me that her and Jonathan-who has but 2 months ago ripped my heart out- have "been seeing each other", even though she" never planned for it to work out like this," and is "sorry" and what not.

So here I stand, alone. One of the two pillars of strength I had in my life is now gone, for there is no way that this action can be forgiven. As you so often said, Nina, "Fuck me once, shame on you. Fuck me twice, shame on me." There wont be a third. For now there is nothing but animosity between us. Well, animosity from me anyway. A blatent stab in the back...from one of the very few people I have allowed to travel deep inside me. And in such a short amount of time after the other...2+2=4. I can't help now but assume you had part in that event, too. I'd thought it from the beginning, but I had shoved that out of my mind because you were my friend. I want to know how long. How long have you secretly felt this affection towards my own? Why did you act upon it. And how can you possibly concieve of the thought that I would actually ever want to speak to you again. You threw away a friendship I thought was good. Your actions have proved otherwise, and I thank you. Thank you for showing me now what kind of a friend you are. I should have learned the first time. I knew then. But I thought that by changing your father's mind about who stole the money, you had shown enough initiative to rectify the damage that had been done. I don't think there will be any way to rectify the pain you have caused me. The unjustified pain taht you so willingly inflicted. I pray that your relationship with Jonathan lasts, or else you will have just made one of the biggest mistakes of your life.
Oh yeah...my birthday's Friday...turning 19...so if anyone forgets- I will disown you as a friend. No shit.

I have been very productive today. I...called WaHo and told them to send me my W2 form or face inquiry by the IRS...finished filling out my GS application/sent it in...got notes for my midterm exam in Water Aerobics...and found out my roommate was a bitch to yet another of my friends. It is sad that at a campus of over 22,000 ppl...one person can be thought of as a bitch to so many people. It makes me feel less guilty about hating her, knowing that many others find her to be a nasty bitch. On another note, I've found that I have become severly distrustful of everyone. I'm tired of being nice to people who don't realize they treat me like shit. I think I've almost gotten to the point where I'm over him. I still dream about him...and these dreams always lead to a day of crying and depression, but I'm doing fairly well at not thinking about it consciously.

It seems as though I only write when I'm depressed. I'm not so much now, but I was earlier. I'm so tired of fighting this battle seemingly alone. Although today was rocky, I had a wonderful time Sat night. Nina, Matt and I all went to Grand Central Station-my first straight club. It was odd having the boys dance with me as opposed to each other. I had to be saved from an asian in a cowboy hat wearing a black spandexy muscle shirt. Ironically, I had been checking him out from afar earlier, thinking he was a cute little dyke. So sadly mistaken. I wanted to check out the 1st floor- which is like Coyote Ugly with the hot bartenders dancing and pouring water all down their fronts. I am so very very sore from working out for the first time in months and then dancing the next night. I have homework I should do, but I'd rather just pass the fuck out. Seeing as how I didn't get too much sleep last night, I think I will do just that.

I feel like I'm spreading myself too thin. Or maybe there just wasn't much left in the jar to begin with. I wish I could purge from my mind all that is dark and malefic so that I may once again embrace life with an open mind, free of fear. I'm always so tired. It's as if even my body is telling me how pointless it is to get out of bed. I don't understand why I'm getting so much worse. I guess because my situation is still the same. I try so hard to be happy. It's usually just a temporary fix. I don't really know how to fit the pieces back.

Ok-forewarning- i'me so drunk. but this dude hit onme alll night. he walked me back to my dorm. He asked for a goodnight kiss in a scottish accent. i said i had made poor descions while drunk before, so no thanks. I wanted it, but i said no. for that, i am proud of myself.

I'm tired of bad dreams that revolve around the same person. I'm sick of tossing and turning at night. I'm sick of waking up feeling like shit because of the wild games my subconscious likes to play. I'm sick of the tension. I'm sick of this hopeless feeling. 
And I cant just ignore any of it.

When I'm here, I want to go home. Sometimes, when I'm home, I'd rather be here. Home is most definitely the lesser of two evils; at home I have my mom and Nina- and a private bedroom and bathroom.
I have no haven here.
fuck the inauguration- i want to watch bob barker's sexy ass giving away money and prizes. tomorrow, i get to go home. i havent cried yet this week, so i spose all is going as well as possible.

If you're still reading this-stop. You don't care to have me in your life, so you sure as hell don't deserve to know about mine.
I hate this place. I really hate this place.

I'm trying to be positive, even if it doesn't seem possible. My entire life has changed yet again. I think I'm overdue for some stability. I made the Dean's List. It's funny, the similarities you can still find between college and high school. Same shit, different day. I think I'll go work on the modified plan for my future some more. A plan is always good to have. Gives you something to look foward to.

I can feel it affecting my body; my stomach is  knotted and aflame. I can feel myself slipping away. I could taste it on my tounge, a beckoning from my Id. Then the visualization so vivid. I want to give up and let it take me away as just another memory in the wind.

So- I woke up at 1, got the the library at 1:45 and studied my ass off basically the whole day. Jonathan never called, as I told him to. He probably forgot. I know he could have, though- he talked to Nina. I drank many Red Bulls and Starbucks double shot frapiccino things. I became very hyperactive/ delerious. I finished studying w/Logan. I think I will do well. I smoked a bowl. I was given a like 12-14 oz beer. I am mellow and hyper at the same time. I know thats completely oxymoronic...but oh well.

I don't feel like the star anymore; I'm just a blurred character in the background. I think of all the special things I once had and wonder if they ever truly were for me. Everything that once was feels as though it was never meant to be as special as I thought it was. I feel like a fool, a jelous fool. I wish I could just divert my attention to the other and feel rage and hatred, but this could never be- it's not her fault. I don't feel as though I belong anywhere now. I have no place where everything is ok, no matter what. I wish it didn't hurt because it shouldn't. But then again, I do have my  justified reasons. The others I'm sure are overanalyized exaggerations.
Either way, the pain is real and I wish it'd go away.

This makes biking through puddles an adventure b/c you never know how hight he splash will go!
Damn rain- go away!!!!!
